                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-104-victim870 t18180909-104-viclabel579"></join>, and lives at <placeName id="t18180909-104-crimeloc580">Sparrow-corner</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-104-crimeloc580" type="placeName" value="Sparrow-corner"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-104-crimeloc580" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-104-off577 t18180909-104-crimeloc580"></join>. On the 14th of July, about one o'clock, the prisoner came into the shop, and sold me an old coat for 2s. 6d., he sent me for a pot of beer; he sat in the shop by himself while I was gone. I returned in about two minutes, and found him gone with the property; he had been stopped with it while I was gone.</p>
               <p>JOHN BARRON. I live next door to the prosecutor. I saw the prisoner sitting by himself in the shop, and saw Hollard go to the public-house. He was hardly out of sight before the prisoner came out with some clothes. I followed the prisoner, and secured him with them.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was intoxicated.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180909-104-verdict581" type="verdictDescription">
